{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1891d87a-c3aa-4c0d-aef0-9a1435ec26f4","content":"Your project isn't present in this workspace, but here's how to configure it.\n\nCreate or edit `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`command`/`args`** — Uses `dotnet run` to build and launch your project.\n- Your server must use **stdio transport** (not HTTP/SSE). If using the [C# MCP SDK](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/csharp-sdk), configure it with `.WithStdioServerTransport()`.\n- After saving, open the **Copilot Chat** panel in agent mode (`@workspace`), and VS Code will auto-start the server.\n\n**For production builds** (faster startup), replace with:\n\n```json\n\"command\": \"dotnet\",\n\"args\": [\"exec\", \"src/MyMcpServer/bin/Release/net8.0/MyMcpServer.dll\"]\n```\n\n(Run `dotnet build -c Release` first.)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"66f47a67-730b-4344-a980-205781fb1995","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist, but the user is asking for configuration guidance, not for me to build anything. I can still answer their question about how to configure `mcp.json`.","outputTokens":389,"requestId":"CBC0:19BCF6:17D137C:1B150FF:69FE8944"},"id":"214a035f-33e5-4ea2-991a-7a79b2bbb8f9","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:09:33.565Z","parentId":"36f953a6-cef5-4ca8-a60f-8aae2da12210"}
